# Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Date: [Offer Date]

To: [Candidate Name]  
Address: [Candidate Address]

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the position of **AI Intern**. This document outlines the key terms of the internship. Please review and confirm your acceptance by signing in the space provided at the end of this letter.

## 1. Position and Company
- Position: AI Intern  
- Company: Omninuera

## 2. Duration and Start Date
- Duration: 3 months.  
- Start Date: To be mutually agreed (placeholder: **[Start Date]**).

## 3. Compensation
- Stipend: **INR 10,000 per month (stipend)**.  
- Payment schedule: Stipend will be paid monthly in arrears upon submission of timesheet and any required onboarding paperwork.

## 4. Work Location and Hours
- Work location: Completely remote. For jurisdiction reference, the candidate is based in **Bengaluru**.  
- Employment type: Internship (temporary).  
- Expected weekly hours: **20 hours/week** (part-time). Actual schedule to be agreed with your Reporting Manager.

## 5. Reporting Line and Department
- Department: [Department]  
- Reporting Manager: You will report directly to **[Reporting Manager Name]** (or their delegate).

## 6. Nature of Engagement
- This internship is a temporary, educational, and developmental arrangement intended to provide practical work experience. It does not constitute a guarantee of future employment.
- The internship is part-time (expected 20 hours/week) unless otherwise agreed in writing.

## 7. Probation and Termination
- As this is an internship, formal probation is not applicable in the same manner as for permanent employees. Your performance and fit will be reviewed during the internship period.
- Either you or Omninuera may terminate the internship at any time. We request a notice period of at least **7 days** where practicable, but Omninuera reserves the right to end the internship immediately for cause or where operational needs require it.

## 8. Confidentiality
- During and after the internship, you must maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera's proprietary and confidential information. You must not disclose, use, or permit the use of such information except as authorized by Omninuera in connection with your internship duties.

## 9. Intellectual Property (IP) Assignment
- You acknowledge and agree that any inventions, designs, works of authorship, discoveries, ideas, improvements, or other creations related to Omninuera’s business that you create, develop, or reduce to practice during the internship (whether alone or with others) shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. You agree to disclose such creations promptly and to execute documents necessary to assign and transfer any rights to Omninuera as reasonably requested.

## 10. Compliance with Company Policies
- You are expected to comply with all Omninuera policies, including but not limited to code of conduct, IT and data security policies, acceptable use, and anti-discrimination and harassment policies. Violation of company policies may result in corrective action up to and including termination of the internship.

## 11. Background Checks and Pre-employment Requirements
- This offer is conditional upon satisfactory completion of any background checks or verifications that Omninuera may require (e.g., academic or employment verification), where applicable.
- You may also be required to complete onboarding documentation and provide identity and address proofs as part of joining formalities.

## 12. Statutory Benefits and Disclaimers (India)
- This is a stipend-based internship. The stipend is intended to cover participation for the agreed internship period. Unless expressly required by applicable law, this internship does not entitle you to salary, provident fund, gratuity, paid leave, or other statutory employment benefits afforded to permanent employees.
- Any statutory benefits or entitlements required under applicable Indian law that apply to internships will be provided as required by law. This paragraph is for HR information only.

## 13. Health and Safety
- You are expected to maintain your own health and personal insurance as needed. Omninuera will provide guidance on any company-specific health and safety requirements applicable to remote work.

## 14. Data Protection
- You must handle personal data in accordance with Omninuera’s data protection policies and applicable laws. Personal data accessed in the course of your work must be used only for legitimate business purposes.

## 15. Acceptance
If you agree to the terms above, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of the signed document to [HR Email] by **[Acceptance Deadline]** (if applicable).

